Return a valid JSON object with the following structure:

```json
{
  "metadata": {
    "title": "string",
    "date_created": "YYYY-MM-DD",
    "author": "string",
    "document_type": "string"
  },
  "entities": {
    "organizations": ["string"],
    "people": [{
      "name": "string",
      "role": "string"
    }],
    "dates": ["YYYY-MM-DD"],
    "amounts": [{
      "value": number,
      "currency": "string",
      "context": "string"
    }]
  },
  "content": {
    "summary": "string",
    "key_points": ["string"],
    "topics": ["string"]
  },
  "custom": {
    "status": "string",
    "priority": "string",
    "notes": "string"
  }
}
```

Ensure the JSON is valid and complete. All fields must be present, use null if not applicable.
